ly blends singleplayer and multiplayer elements to offer a realistic and plausible approach of the backrooms concept. The singleplayer part features the way you reach \"The Loop\", while the multiplayer part allows up to four unfortunate souls to work together in order to escape. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2493670/extras/190781db56fa18633a0e7f66c104f2ae.poster.avif?t=1739827717\" width=620 height=254 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2493670/extras/190781db56fa18633a0e7f66c104f2ae.webm?t=1739827717\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2493670/extras/190781db56fa18633a0e7f66c104f2ae.mp4?t=1739827717\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >The Levels</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Deja Vu</strong> features two kinds of levels:</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > <strong>Procedurally generated levels</strong>, which are completely random and different every time.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > <strong>Static levels</strong>, which are <i>puzzle-based</i> and focus more on exploration and adventure, offering a <i>never-before-seen</i> approach to the backrooms.</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2493670/extras/d4d1388b4239c56df88db09c9ba920bf.poster.avif?t=1739827717\" width=620 height=254 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2493670/extras/d4d1388b4239c56df88db09c9ba920bf.webm?t=1739827717\" type=\"vid